#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:4
msgid "Installing Mattermost Server"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:6
msgid "Install Mattermost Server on a 64-bit machine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:8
msgid "Assume that the IP address of this server is 10.10.10.2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:10
msgid "**To install Mattermost Server on Debian Buster**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:12
msgid ""
"Log in to the server that will host Mattermost Server and open a terminal"
" window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:14
msgid ""
"Download `the latest version of the Mattermost Server "
"<https://about.mattermost.com/download/>`__. In the following command, "
"replace ``X.X.X`` with the version that you want to download:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:16
msgid ""
"``wget https://releases.mattermost.com/X.X.X/mattermost-X.X.X-linux-"
"amd64.tar.gz``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:18
msgid "Extract the Mattermost Server files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:20
msgid "``tar -xvzf mattermost*.gz``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:22
msgid "Move the extracted file to the ``/opt`` directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:24
msgid "``sudo mv mattermost /opt``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:26
msgid "Create the storage directory for files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:28
msgid "``sudo mkdir /opt/mattermost/data``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:31
msgid ""
"The storage directory will contain all the files and images that your "
"users post to Mattermost, so you need to make sure that the drive is "
"large enough to hold the anticipated number of uploaded files and images."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:33
msgid ""
"Set up a system user and group called ``mattermost`` that will run this "
"service, and set the ownership and permissions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:35
msgid "Create the Mattermost user and group:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:36
msgid "``sudo useradd --system --user-group mattermost``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:37
msgid "Set the user and group *mattermost* as the owner of the Mattermost files:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:38
msgid "``sudo chown -R mattermost:mattermost /opt/mattermost``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:39
msgid "Give write permissions to the *mattermost* group:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:40
msgid "``sudo chmod -R g+w /opt/mattermost``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:42
msgid ""
"Set up the database driver in the file "
"``/opt/mattermost/config/config.json``. Open the file in a text editor "
"and make the following changes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:44
msgid "If you are using PostgreSQL:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:45
msgid "Set ``\"DriverName\"`` to ``\"postgres\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:46
msgid ""
"Set ``\"DataSource\"`` to the following value, replacing ``<mmuser-"
"password>``  and ``<host-name-or-IP>`` with the appropriate values:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:47
msgid ""
"``\"postgres://mmuser:<mmuser-password>@<host-name-or-"
"IP>:5432/mattermost?sslmode=disable&connect_timeout=10\",``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:48
msgid "If you are using MySQL:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:49
msgid "Set ``\"DriverName\"`` to ``\"mysql\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:50
msgid ""
"Set ``\"DataSource\"`` to the following value, replacing ``<mmuser-"
"password>``  and ``<host-name-or-IP>`` with the appropriate values. Also "
"make sure that the database name is ``mattermost`` instead of "
"``mattermost_test``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:51
msgid ""
"``\"mmuser:<mmuser-password>@tcp(<host-name-or-"
"IP>:3306)/mattermost?charset=utf8mb4,utf8&readTimeout=30s&writeTimeout=30s\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:53
msgid "Test the Mattermost server to make sure everything works."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:55
msgid "Change to the ``bin`` directory:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:56
msgid "``cd /opt/mattermost``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:57
msgid "Start the Mattermost server as the user mattermost:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:58
msgid "``sudo -u mattermost ./bin/mattermost``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:60
msgid ""
"When the server starts, it shows some log information and the text "
"``Server is listening on :8065``. You can stop the server by pressing "
"CTRL+C in the terminal window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:62
msgid "Setup Mattermost to use *systemd* for starting and stopping."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:64
msgid "Create a *systemd* unit file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:65
msgid "``sudo touch /lib/systemd/system/mattermost.service``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:66
msgid ""
"Open the unit file as root in a text editor, and copy the following lines"
" into the file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:91
msgid ""
"If you are using MySQL, replace ``postgresql.service`` with "
"``mysql.service`` in 2 places in the ``[Unit]`` section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:94
msgid ""
"If you have installed MySQL or PostgreSQL on a dedicated server then you "
"need to remove the ``After=postgresql.service`` and "
"``Requires=postgresql.service`` or ``After=mysql.service`` and "
"``Requires=mysql.service`` lines in the ``[Unit]`` section or the "
"Mattermost service will not start."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:96
msgid "Make systemd load the new unit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:98
msgid "``sudo systemctl daemon-reload``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:100
msgid "Check to make sure that the unit was loaded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:102
msgid "``sudo systemctl status mattermost.service``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:104
msgid "You should see an output similar to the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:112
msgid "Start the service."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:114
msgid "``sudo systemctl start mattermost.service``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:116
msgid "Verify that Mattermost is running."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:118
msgid "``curl http://localhost:8065``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:120
msgid "You should see the HTML that's returned by the Mattermost server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:122
msgid "Set Mattermost to start on machine start up."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:124
msgid "``sudo systemctl enable mattermost.service``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/install/install-debian-mattermost.rst:126
msgid ""
"Now that the Mattermost server is up and running, you can do some initial"
" configuration and setup."
msgstr ""

